More than 5,000 pupils will resume classes after schools were shut down for two weeks due to banditry attacks in Baringo county. Speaking in Kabarnet town on Monday, Rift Valley regional coordinator Wanyama Musiambo said there is no violence.Musiambo said 2,361 pupils have resumed classes in Baringo North and South subcounties. Some 39 primary schools and ECD centres were closed.